goals.question: What is the average income for each region?
goals.visualization: bar chart of total income by region
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to compare the income of different regions and identify the regions with the highest and lowest income.

goals.question: What is the distribution of income percentages across all regions?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to identify the most common income percentages and the range of income percentages across all regions.

goals.question: What is the relationship between income percentage and income group?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of income percentage and income group
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to identify any patterns or trends between income percentage and income group.

goals.question: What is the distribution of income groups across all regions?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to identify the most common income groups and the proportion of each income group across all regions.

goals.question: What is the relationship between region and income group?
goals.visualization: stacked bar chart of income groups by region
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to compare the income groups of different regions and identify any regional patterns or trends.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='region', y='total', data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average income for each region?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='pct', kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Income Percentages')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income percentages across all regions?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='group', y='pct', data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    income_group_counts = data['group'].value_counts()
    chart = sns.pieplot(x=income_group_counts.values, labels=income_group_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    chart.set_xlabel('Income Group')
    chart.set_ylabel('Percentage')
    chart.xaxis.label.set_rotation(45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income groups across all regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
